DataElement.preferredDefinition: The study of the structure of the cells and their arrangement to constitute tissues and, finally, the association among these to form organs.  In pathology, the microscopic process of identifying normal and abnormal morphologic characteristics in tissues, by employing various cytochemical and immunocytochemical stains._The extent of a cancer within the body, especially whether the disease has spread from the original site to other parts of the body._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
